<plot>Robert Benchley takes off from work early to go home and surprise his wife. He gets the surprise when he arrives and discovers his wife is hosting a bridge-party, and the house is filled with chattering women. He goes upstairs and finds Junior sulking there. A trip to the cellar leads to Benchley taking several samples of home-brew, and then decides that putting on an Indian costume and going upstairs whooping and brandishing a tomahawk will be amusing to his wife and her friends. It isn't.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?243873</url></doc>
